  "Stéphane Bancel, 47, is the CEO of Cambridge, Massachusetts-based biotech firm Moderna Therapeutics. ",
  "He owns a roughly 9% stake in the publicly traded company and became CEO in 2011.",
  "Before joining Moderna, Bancel was the CEO of French diagnostics company BioMérieux, founded by fellow French billionaire Alain Mérieux.",
  "Moderna was the first company to begin human trials of its vaccine for COVID-19, on March 16, 2020 in Seattle.",
  "Moderna was founded in 2010 and went public in December 2018; the company develops drugs and vaccines using messenger RNA."
